		<div id="siteNotice"><script type='text/javascript'>if (wgNotice != '') document.writeln(wgNotice);</script></div>		<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading">Pretty Good Privacy</h1>
		<div id="bodyContent">
			<h3 id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</h3>
			<div id="contentSub"></div>
									<div id="jump-to-nav">Jump to: <a href="#column-one">navigation</a>, <a href="#searchInput">search</a></div>			<!-- start content -->
			<p><b>Pretty Good Privacy</b> (<b>PGP</b>) is a <a href="/wiki/Computer_program" title="Computer program">computer program</a> that provides <a href="/wiki/Cryptographic" title="Cryptographic" class="mw-redirect">cryptographic</a> <a href="/wiki/Privacy" title="Privacy">privacy</a> and <a href="/wiki/Authentication" title="Authentication">authentication</a>. PGP is often used for signing, encrypting and decrypting e-mails to increase the security of e-mail communications. It was originally created by <a href="/wiki/Philip_Zimmermann" title="Philip Zimmermann" class="mw-redirect">Philip Zimmermann</a> in 1991.</p>
<p>PGP and other similar products follow the <a href="/wiki/OpenPGP" title="OpenPGP" class="mw-redirect">OpenPGP</a> standard (<a href="http://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc4880" class="external" title="http://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc4880">RFC 4880</a>) for encrypting and decrypting data.</p>
